# Default: treat as text, normalize to LF on commit, check out as LF on
# every platform. Windows tools (Node, Python, IDEs, modern PowerShell)
# all handle LF source files correctly; pinning eol=lf eliminates the
# Windows-checkout CRLF noise that would otherwise leave files
# perpetually `M` in `git status` (T-041 hit this on aliases/motions
# components).
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary files: never normalize, never diff as text. Lists the formats
# the repo actually carries (api/app/ai/_fixtures/* + future image /
# video / font assets).
*.png      binary
*.jpg      binary
*.jpeg     binary
*.gif      binary
*.webp     binary
*.ico      binary
*.bmp      binary
*.svg      text eol=lf
*.mp4      binary
*.webm     binary
*.mov      binary
*.mp3      binary
*.wav      binary
*.woff     binary
*.woff2    binary
*.ttf      binary
*.otf      binary
*.eot      binary
*.pdf      binary
*.zip      binary
*.gz       binary
*.tar      binary
*.tgz      binary
*.7z       binary
*.db       binary
*.sqlite   binary
*.sqlite3  binary

# Lock files: text but never collapse line-by-line in PR diffs (GitHub
# already does this; the marker also helps `git log -p`).
pnpm-lock.yaml -diff
package-lock.json -diff
poetry.lock -diff
